they can think about.

00:08:15,551 --> 00:08:18,531
That consumes them.
That eats them,

00:08:18,531 --> 00:08:19,543
and that's the way
you have to be.

00:08:19,543 --> 00:08:20,553
You have to work
like there's somebody

00:08:20,553 --> 00:08:22,531
trying to take it
all away from you,

00:08:22,531 --> 00:08:24,528
because there probably is.

00:08:24,528 --> 00:08:25,544
My suggestion is

00:08:25,544 --> 00:08:26,551
get somebody else
to sell it for you,

00:08:26,551 --> 00:08:28,529
because that is not
your strength.

00:08:28,529 --> 00:08:30,867
You're not an entrepreneur.
You're a want-repreneur,

00:08:30,867 --> 00:08:32,858
and for that reason,
I'm out.

00:08:32,858 --> 00:08:36,867
Okay, well, thank you.
I disagree with you, though.

00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:38,865
Who's left?
Lori.

00:08:38,865 --> 00:08:43,849
Well, I don't agree
with Mark or Barb

00:08:43,849 --> 00:08:46,845
that you need
to go down to one bottle.

00:08:46,845 --> 00:08:50,849
They're mistaken because they're
not retail people like I am.

00:08:50,849 --> 00:08:53,868
I think your creativity
is fantastic. I love this.

00:08:53,868 --> 00:08:57,859
I think it's super sweet.

00:08:57,859 --> 00:09:01,849
The problem is, is you haven't
gone and really tried,

00:09:01,849 --> 00:09:04,872
I don't think hard enough,
to make your dream come true.

00:09:06,854 --> 00:09:08,845
I'm out.
Okay, well,

00:09:08,845 --> 00:09:10,866
thank you guys so much
for your time. Thank you.
(Mark) Good luck, Debbie.

00:09:10,866 --> 00:09:12,862
(Lori) Good luck.
Thanks.

00:09:12,862 --> 00:09:14,849
